task.summary: Initial commit Transitioning from verbal setup to visual only.
Added MyPillow.py and started to create functions for image comparison like added, subtracted, same, different.
Got enough in place to solve problems without transforms now. Need to implement method to determine transforms. Need to implement method to apply transforms for solutions.
Added Transform.py and built method to return transform options.

Finished version 1 code for capturing transforms, applying transforms to generate solutions, and testing solutions. Also added logic to choose between horizontal and vertical transforms based on ease.
Added logic to solve problem iteratively so we don't try everything all the time. Also added a fuzzify method to MyPillow that returns a "blurred" version of the image.
Added a few small files - most notably the corner-reduce image to git.
Refactoring to meet PEP8 standards better, and put in loading of extra images and answers for 3x3 problems.
Have the function in place to measure black pixel count difference and also to measure black pixel match rate.
Progression anlysis is now in place with the addition of PixelAnalysis and PixelAnalysisAnalysis. This method takes care of 9 of the twelve basic problems.
Implemented OR and Pixel Summation solutions for 3x3 problems to make progress on the D and E sets.
Fine-tuned 3x3 methods to increase accuracy. In a pretty good spot now, so time to implement a new solution method.
Added an AB pixel subtraction method that solves two E basic problems.
Added methods that check region summation and uniqueness and filter available answers before progression (final method). More problems solved and accuracy improved.
